Hello guys,
i'm autistic myself.

Autistic or other "disabled" people should be played by autistic or "disabled" people! Not by neurotypicals. It's just insulting and patronizing if autistic people are played by neurotypicals. Even if a "name" means funding. Movie companies have collected hundred when not even trillions of Dollars, plus attention and compliments with obviously autistic characters or characters with autistic traits. Same is for other "disabled" people. It's time that the so called disabled themselves are getting included!

It's good that there are more and more TV-shows and movies with "disabled" persons, because with that, Neurotypicals can familiarize with (fictional) autists or other "disabled persons" and some kind of their behaviour, which will spread awareness for them. But: The "disabled" themselves are still excluded.

Don't play me pay me! And also have a nice day. ;)

For further information see the links below. Please like so that hopefully somebody with influence can see this information. Thank you.
